'''Kenneth L. Hanson''' (born 1953) is an associate professor in the University of Central Florida Judaic Studies Program, at the [[University of Central Florida]], in [[Orlando, Florida]]. Dr. Hanson has authored books on [[Dead Sea scrolls|the Dead Sea Scrolls]], [[Kabbalah]] and lost books of the Bible. He is a regular contributor on [[History (U.S. TV channel)|the History Channel]], and.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.treasuresintime.org/Site/Welcome.html|title=Dr. Kenneth Hanson|publisher=Treasures in Time|accessdate=14 December 2010}}</ref> has also appeared on the radio show [[Coast to Coast AM]] as a guest numerous times.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coasttocoastam.com/guest/hanson-dr-kenneth/5951|title=Dr. Kenneth Hanson - Guests|publisher=Coast to Coast AM|accessdate=10 December 2010}}</ref>
He is famous for his characters and impersonations, noted is his excellent portrayal of Sherlock Holmes.
